reviews.text: A hidden gem. Great food quality, decent price. Come here for their lunch menu, if u want Korean food. U won't be disappointed

Food: 6 out of 5
Service: 4 out of 5

As always, food is superb and it all starts with side dishes.  Not for once I got disappointed here.  I note from a local food critics website that some people complained about its service.  In my experience visiting this place 10+ times, the floor staff are always reasonably polite.  I can only hope that they are more attentive.  Food is so good that I can live with the less than perfect service.  I like Korean food but am no expert to judge the authenticity here.  Guess it is rather authentic when most of the time there are Korean-speaking diners here.

This place is here for a long time and it used to be quite popular. First time here and the place was not half filled. Took quite a while to get the attention of waitresses to take the order. Got a fried seafood pancake and a kimchi pork stew. Quality was good. Sadly the waitstaff seemed a little uninterested in serving customers. When asked, was told only two of the small dish appetizers could be refilled - first time ever in a Korean restaurant! And never did the refills arrive too... That speaks a lot about its service, and I'm no longer surprised at its pathetic occupancy at dinner time.

There are so many Korean restaurants in the Tsim Sha Tsui area and I rate this one as above-the-average. If you visit this restaurant, try the spicy pot with octopus and beef, which I don’t found in the other Korean restaurants around.

Korean Food that taste better than the ones I had in Korea~! Highly recommend this place!!
Ambience, quality of food, service all deserves a high score. 
A bit pricy, but what isn't in HK~! Dining in this Korean restaurant is well worth your money and time.
